Rep Approach: â€¢ Discuss the importance of assessing renal function (eGFR, CrCl) before PrEP initiation and every 3-6 months during treatment, as recommended for safe PrEP prescribing practices [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].  â€¢ Highlight the need for regular monitoring to ensure the safe use of PrEP in patients with pre-existing renal impairment, as indicated in the FDA label [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].  â€¢ Emphasize the importance of dose adjustment or discontinuation if eGFR <50 mL/min, to prevent renal toxicity and ensure patient safety, as per the FDA label [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].

Impact: By emphasizing the importance of regular renal function monitoring, the HCP will be more likely to prioritize safe PrEP prescribing practices and adapt treatment plans as needed.

Suggested Phrasing: "To ensure safe PrEP prescribing, I recommend we monitor renal function every 3-6 months, and consider dose adjustment or discontinuation if eGFR <50 mL/min, as indicated in the FDA label. "

Rep Approach: â€¢ Discuss the importance of regular renal function assessment to ensure safe PrEP prescribing practices, as recommended to be every 3-6 months during treatment [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].  â€¢ Highlight the need for ongoing monitoring to adjust or discontinue PrEP if eGFR thresholds are not met, as indicated in the FDA label for Descovy [HIV-PREP-TAF-002].  â€¢ Emphasize the importance of considering individual patient factors, such as comorbidities and medication regimens, to inform renal function monitoring and PrEP management [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].

Impact: By emphasizing the importance of regular renal function monitoring, the HCP will be more likely to prioritize ongoing assessment and adjust PrEP prescribing practices as needed to ensure patient safety.

Rep Approach: â€¢ Discuss the importance of assessing renal function (eGFR, CrCl) and urinalysis before PrEP initiation and monitoring every 3-6 months during treatment, as recommended for safe PrEP prescribing [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].  â€¢ Highlight the need for regular monitoring to identify potential renal issues early, as indicated in the FDA label for Descovy PrEP [HIV-PREP-TAF-002].  â€¢ Emphasize the importance of dose adjustment or discontinuation if eGFR <50 mL/min, per the FDA label, to ensure safe and effective PrEP treatment [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].

Impact: By emphasizing the importance of regular renal function monitoring, the HCP will be more likely to prioritize safe PrEP prescribing and adapt treatment plans as needed.

Suggested Phrasing: "To ensure safe and effective PrEP treatment, I recommend we monitor renal function every 3-6 months and adjust or discontinue treatment if eGFR falls below 50 mL/min, as indicated in the FDA label. "

Rep Approach: â€¢ Discuss the importance of monitoring renal function every 3-6 months during PrEP treatment to ensure safe prescribing practices, as recommended [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].  â€¢ Highlight the need for ongoing renal function assessment to identify potential kidney issues early, particularly in patients with pre-existing kidney disease or risk factors [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].  â€¢ Emphasize the importance of considering dose adjustment or discontinuation if eGFR <50 mL/min, as per the FDA label, to prevent kidney damage [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].

Impact: By emphasizing the importance of regular renal function monitoring, the HCP will be more likely to prioritize ongoing assessment and adjust PrEP treatment as needed to prevent kidney damage.

Impact: By monitoring renal function regularly, the HCP will be able to identify potential issues early and adjust PrEP treatment accordingly, ensuring safe and effective treatment for patients.

Suggested Phrasing: "To ensure safe prescribing practices, I recommend monitoring renal function every 3-6 months during PrEP treatment, including regular urinalysis and eGFR assessments, and adjusting treatment as needed based on eGFR thresholds. "

Rep Approach: â€¢ Discuss the importance of assessing renal function (eGFR, CrCl) before PrEP initiation and monitoring every 3-6 months during treatment, as recommended for safe prescribing practices [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].  â€¢ Highlight the need for regular monitoring to ensure the safe use of PrEP in patients with pre-existing renal impairment, as indicated in the FDA label [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].  â€¢ Emphasize the importance of dose adjustment or discontinuation if eGFR <50 mL/min, to prevent renal toxicity and ensure patient safety, as per the FDA label [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].

Impact: By emphasizing the importance of regular renal function monitoring, the HCP will be more likely to prioritize safe prescribing practices and adjust treatment plans as needed to prevent renal toxicity.

Suggested Phrasing: "To ensure the safe use of PrEP, I recommend we monitor renal function every 3-6 months, and consider dose adjustment or discontinuation if eGFR <50 mL/min, as indicated in the FDA label. "

Rep Approach: â€¢ Discuss the importance of regular renal function assessment before and during PrEP, as recommended to monitor for potential renal impairment [HIV-PREP-SAFETY-003].  â€¢ Highlight the need for monitoring renal function every 3-6 months during PrEP treatment, as indicated in the clinical guidelines, to ensure safe prescribing practices.  â€¢ Emphasize the need to consider dose adjustment or discontinuation if eGFR is less than 50 mL/min, per the FDA label, to protect patient kidney health.

Impact: By emphasizing the importance of regular renal function monitoring, the HCP will be more likely to prioritize patient safety and adjust PrEP treatment plans accordingly.
